text:
@ZaStocks @bull_jared39128 what do you like?
And do you see the hype catching before the next year? 
i think the photonics and semis have still room to run and then after SPCX IPO markets cools off

AI’s Connectivity Revolution Is Here — And It’s All About Photonics!  Gemini Trading just dropped a crystal-clear infographic that maps exactly how next-gen AI computing clusters are breaking through the electrical bottleneck.  From massive GPU server farms (1) to high-speed SerDes links on PCBs (2), traditional copper can’t keep up with exploding bandwidth demands. Enter the star of the show: Co-Packaged Optics (CPO) (3). By integrating Laser and Photonic Integrated Circuit (PIC) directly beside the Switch ASIC, CPO slashes electrical travel distance, cuts power loss, and delivers ultra-low latency at insane speeds.  Compare that to legacy pluggable optical modules (4) — bulkier, hotter, and less efficient. Then watch the magic happen in (5): fiber links extend connectivity from inside the rack (<2 m) across racks (2–30 m), floors (30 m–2 km), and even global data centers (2 km–2000+ km).  The bottom panel perfectly visualizes the E-O-E journey: electrical signals → light via laser → optical fiber → back to electrical. Short-range stays electric; long-haul goes photonic. Result? Dramatically lower energy use, higher bandwidth, and sustainable scaling for trillion-parameter AI models.  This isn’t hype — it’s the infrastructure upgrade the entire AI industry needs. Hyperscalers, chip designers, and data-center operators are already racing toward CPO adoption.  At Gemini Trading we track these photonics breakthroughs because they don’t just move data — they move markets.  What’s your take? Will CPO become the new standard in 2026–2027? Drop your thoughts below!   @GeminiTrading
 @NVIDIA
 @Broadcom

#CPO #Photonics #AI #DataCenter #Semiconductors #TechInnovation #GeminiTrading  (Share this infographic and tag a friend building the future!)

